"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function sns.set_context does not have an rc argument. The function sns.set_style has an rc argument but it should be used with a dictionary of parameters that are part of the style definition. The higher-level function sns.set_theme can be used with a dictionary of any matplotlib parameters.\", \"patch\": \"8,14c8,9\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n< style_dict = {\\n<     'axes.grid': True,\\n<     'grid.color': 'red'\\n< }\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_theme(rc={**scale_dict, **style_dict})\\n> sns.set_context('notebook')\\n\"}"